io.github.utk003.util.misc

Class Verifier

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.utk003.util.misc.Verifier

  • @ScheduledForRelease(inVersion="v3.0.0")
public abstract class Verifier
extends Object
    An abstract utility class for verification functions.

    This class provides methods for:

    • Failing immediately with either a VerificationException, a VerifierFailedInstantiationException, or a specified Exception subclass,
    • Checking if a condition is true or false,
    • Checking if an object is null or not-null,
    • Checking if two primitives are equal,
    • Checking if two objects are equal via Object.equals(Object),
    • And checking if two object pointers are equal (using ==).

    Any call to this class's verification method(s) can specify any combination of a String error message and an Exception subclass as the mode of failure for that single verification. Alternatively, the call can simply provide an Exception instance for the method to throw in case of failure.
